# Component Structure and Conventions

## Organization
- All Vue components are located in [src/components/](mdc:src/components), organized by feature or function:
  - [application/](mdc:src/components/application): App-level components (e.g., [Chat.vue](mdc:src/components/application/Chat.vue)).
  - [chat/](mdc:src/components/chat): Chat-related components (e.g., [ChatWindow.vue](mdc:src/components/chat/ChatWindow.vue)).
  - [common/](mdc:src/components/common): Common UI components (currently empty).
  - [layout/](mdc:src/components/layout): Layout/navigation (e.g., [Layout.vue](mdc:src/components/layout/Layout.vue)).
  - [login/](mdc:src/components/login): Login form component ([LoginForm.vue](mdc:src/components/login/LoginForm.vue)).
  - [utilities/](mdc:src/components/utilities): Utility UI components (e.g., [Prompt.vue](mdc:src/components/utilities/Prompt.vue)), with [connection/](mdc:src/components/utilities/connection) for connection diagnostics.

## Conventions
- Components use the Vue 3 `<script setup>` syntax.
- Use PascalCase for component filenames (e.g., `ChatWindow.vue`).
- Place feature-specific components in their respective subdirectories.
- Common or shared UI components should go in [common/](mdc:src/components/common).
- Layout and navigation components should go in [layout/](mdc:src/components/layout).

## Example
- [ChatWindow.vue](mdc:src/components/chat/ChatWindow.vue): A chat window component.
- [Prompt.vue](mdc:src/components/utilities/Prompt.vue): A utility prompt component.
- [Layout.vue](mdc:src/components/layout/Layout.vue): The main layout component.
